   Seres armipes armipes Waterston and Seres armipes breviceps Wiebes are
   described for the first time. Seres longicephalus Risbec is synonymised
   with S. a armipes Waterston. Seres levis Waterston is omitted, awaiting
   transference to Philocaenus Grandi. A key is provided to separate the
